reviews.review_text: Food is decent, and common restaurant food you would normally find in Hong Kong. The staff is quite friendly even though the restaurant is packed, you almost always need to wait 10 to 30 minutes to get a table. So what makes this attractive to so many people? The size is way more than generous, especially for todays economy in 2023. Be prepared to bring a takeaway box (unless you dont mind paying 50 cents for a paper box from the restaurant). One final note: the default tips amount is less than 15%, which is something you dont see anymore in todays Vancouver.
Food and portions are really good! Prices are reasonable for what you get. I am a big guy and I had to pack some of the food home.

Very unassuming restaurant with clean interior. BIG portion, and fairly priced its the definite stand-out. We got the Laksa with grilled chicken and fish fillet with creamy sauce and spaghetti both are incredibly delicious and filling. The cold drinks (milk tea and lemon tea) are typical run of the mill drinks, tasty and not too sweet.

Gold star to the chef at the grill. The meats here are always executed to technical perfection: juicy and tender with crispy but not greasy skin. Given this is a small restaurant with only 9 tables, Im impressed by the diversity and quality of the food. Furthermore impressed that most meals are at the $10 and $15 price points. Beef and mushroom sandwich: Was eclipsed by the fries, which were prepared my favourite way, with batter and crispy. The sandwich was nice too, lots of beef, tender and cooked medium rare the way I like. Only complaint was that there was some cartilage in the meat, which I had to cut out. Panko-fried pork chops: Again, lots of meat, two chops, which were tender, juicy, and just gently seasoned, the way I like. Chicken rice noodle soup had a perfectly  grilled boneless chicken thigh with crispy skin. Mixed grill: All meats grilled to textural perfection. Enough food for 2 people. Onion gravy good with fries. Service excellent, attentive, friendly, with a personal touch.
All Day Breakfast is my favorite!  Big portion!  There are two pieces of pork chop in the bun.  Very delicious.  Authentic Hong Kong taste.

The portion is big and the crispy bun is a must-try item. Laksa is quite good and could be even better if the coconut flavor is stronger. The portion of pork chop with rice is HUGE and good for sharing. Service is excellent and the owner may walk around and check with each customer on seeking their feedback during the off-peak session. Definitely one of the best value for money restaurant in town.

Fat Boy Kitchen deserves a solid 5-star rating! They serve generous portions, have friendly and attentive staff, and offer an authentic Hong Kong Cafe experience. The laksa is a must-try   you wont be disappointed!

Value for your money. Hidden gem in Vancouver. The place is small so it s not good for a party of 4 or more but even though it s a nice little spot Would recommend eating here during your lunch break or just before dinner. Portions are generous (you would usually pay $5 more somewhere else) This was my 3rd time eating here and haven t been disappointed once!

order the mixed grill steak combo for take-out. comes with beef, pork, chicken steak and cheese sausage. all the meat were fresh and delicious. only thing is they forgot to include the pop. still very good price for the quality. 5 stars! would come back

Wow it s really good old HK fusion cafe.  Food is super tasty, and big portion and great price.  So glad I got to visit it finally.  Hidden gem for sure.  My picture is of curry chicken cutlets and it was huge and tasty, look at it in comparison to the cup.  That was for $17.

This place is small, but food portion is HUGE. Everything cooked to perfection, and the price is great too. Love this place and would like to come more often. But too bad parking is not enough, and this place is always busy. They close on Sunday. Nevertheless this is one of my fav restaurants for good food.
Good Hong Kong style breakfast! Always busy! Pork and chicken cutlet is good!

The food is delicious, the quality & the quantity is above average, most important is the price, cheaper than most of the HK style cafe. The boss & the server are very friendly, they always ask if the customers need anything. The only thing that I concern is they close early at 6:00PM because of the lack of chef, therefore no dinner served, hope they can hire more people to help. According to the overall experience, I will come back for sure.

This place has it all   massive portions, unbeatable prices, and incredible flavors. The service is top-notch, making it an all-around great dining experience. Their number one seller, the chicken steak, seems to be a must-try item, given its popularity. If youre looking for a place that delivers both value and taste, this restaurant seems to have it down to a science.
Amazing HK Breakfast!! Loved the toast!! Recommended if looking for some HK Breakfast

They are amazing   service is kind, quick. Portions are big, quality good. flavor is not extraordinary but I will def. recommend coming often. Prices are pretty good too I had late breakfast (they have an all day breakfast) and the mini soup is huge Beans and eggs yummy also coffee
Yummy food, good value and courteous service. We ordered a chicken laksa soup noodles and all day breakfast. Excellent presentation and taste good. I always love small local businesses.

Attentive Service. Ive been here daily in Late 2021 unless I stopped working around that area. Laska & Satay Noodles were my favourite. When you do find a mistake. They offer to correct it but I just insisted to improve their product without taking a replacement/refund.

I had called into place to ordered dinner for family and myself. Had ordered chicken nuggets on rice combo / black pepper mushroom chicken on rice / hk style milk tea and Iced lemon tea Pros: - good portion per price ratio - the packaging was well done, it was still crispy - service super nice staff and was accommodating Improvement/cons: - Maybe for the restaurant to take pictures of the proper menu and put online so its easier to find. Other than that, pretty happy with the place
Huge portions! Small cozy Hong Kong cafe style restaurant. My favourite is the Taiwanese Chicken Nugget with rice. Must come and try! :)

5 star because every thing comes together for a good experience. I ordered the Satay Beef soup and a side of fries. The soup was huge! Standard flavour and quality. The were also a huge portion. The fries couldve been crispier too, a bit soft for my taste. You might have to wait to get a table. - Great service and staff - Huge portions - Decent food
Good quality and big portions. Everything was flavorful. The fries and chicken nuggets plate was yummy! The restaurant is pretty small so there may be a wait.

I love their curry chicken and lemon ice tea. Its so good that its the only thing I order! Super busy because the food is great and the staff are super friendly. I usually do pick up and eat at a near by park!

We really enjoyed the food today. Generous portions. Flavourful soup noodles - we tried the laksa and the schezwan beef. Huge plate of Taiwanese fried chicken. Yummy HK milk tea. Takeout containers cost 50c each FYI. Friendly efficient service. Was steadily busy even at 2pm. A great find.

I can only speak for the Satay Beef Noodle Soup. I came in expecting a typical HK Cafe meal, but was blown away by how good this bowl of noodles was. The portion of beef was also quite substantial. Their noodle soups are a must-try. My only gripe is the cheap disposable cutlery, but this isnt a major issue.
I have never been disappointed at this restaurant. The food is delicious and very good deal. There is a decent amount of street parking but you may need to walk a block to get here.
Big portion to make you fat. Food is decent and good quality. The only thing I dont like is their use of disposable chopsticks and utensils. Go there at 11am to beat the crowd.

Great deal, right price and delicious Onion Pork Chop with Rice Combo. Come with a soft drink (Add $1.00 if you want to change with hot drink). It has four pieces big pork chop. High end Hong Kong cafeteria style/taste sauce and mouthwatering presentation. I tried another combo (Fat Boy Kitchen Mixed Grill with Rice Combo (sauce on bowl, comes with soft drink) [       ]. I changed rice with Spaghetti. Yummy  .

Hong Kong style comfort food perfected!! So happy to have found this place. Friendly staff, they clean the tables and chairs thoroughly, great food, highly recommend their pork chop bun. Had the chicken laksa and satay beef noodles too but apparently there are 2 different types of satay beef. If you want the hk style one you ll have to let them know. We will be back a lot!

Local family restaurant. Staff here are very nice and speak fluent English and Canto. They were super patient in explaining the menu and offer substitutions for their customers (we ordered French toast off menu, and changed our set toast to an extra hashbrown). Food is awesome. Ju pa bao is very generous portion

If you like HK Cafes, this place is definitely worth trying.  Had my typical black pepper fried chicken with rice.  It was a huge plate of food and it was loaded with sauce (which I love).  Iced lemon tea could use more sweetness, but overall it was a refreshing HK Cafe feel.  I would go again.
One of our family weekend go to place. Great taste great value. Love it. Must try place in East Vancouver.

I went to Fat Boy Kitchen this morning for the first time for a delicious breakfast of pork chops with two eggs and satay beef noodle soup. I was very happy to see a few young people working hard to start their businesses.
Tasty food (and huge servings). Also noteworthy is the staff are very thorough cleaning up the booths. We will definitely be back here.
Big portion delicious food. A La king sauce chicken and Teriyaki very food. Black pepper steak also good! !  Now they open from 9:00 am  5:00 pm from Monday to Friday.

Though the menu is limited, each of the items are quite delicious. I also like their noodle soup and all day breakfast. The base price is quite affordable but there are extra charges for upgrading drinks (or adding a drink for the breakfast).
The portion of the food is pretty good and the portion is pretty big. Good customer service also. Would recommend for breakfast and brunch.
Breakfast with friends, relaxing atmosphere, great simple fare food.  Good service
Great Cantonese cuisine, love the Laksa Parking: Lots of street parking. Really busy during peak hour Food : 5/5 |

I absolutely loved it here! The service was great as soon as I walked through the door. I also did not expect the portions to be THAT BIG!!! I WAS SO AMAZED! Big portions even after covid happened, unbelievable! The food brought tears to my eyes because it tasted SO GOOD
This place makes me feel like home, their services are the best in Vancouver so far      Their food are delicious and I can t wait to come back for more!

The laska is the most delicious laska Ive tasted so far . The staff was very friendly too. The food was in very big portions and was cheap. The hygiene wasnt as exemplary, but the food and service were perfect. The waiting time was also a bit long, but overall, a very promising restaurant. Parking: Only a few parking spots and the front of the restaurant.
Good spread of HK style cafe options. Generous portions and good food. The hk Style milk and ice lemon tea is good.
Overall the food is good. Service was slow but was excellent. Recommend getting the mushroom pepper chicken and HK milk tea. No parking lot, only street parking and it is sometimes hard to find Food

I find this to be a hidden gem since I am a HK cafe food lover.  Quality food and gets full quickly by lunch time due to limited seating.  From milk tea, deep fried dishes or noodles soup, you will not be disappointed.
Service is good and excellent food. Has an affordable price and great portion. Definitely coming back and recommend for people who love Hong Kong style cafes.

Worth the ride/wait for a table. Was good! Services and portions sizes was amazing! Fresh and clean.Small dining ( 10 tables )? wait was not long! ( very well sanitized tables/seats/chairs ( 2 towels for each wipe after each dining ). Server ( Catherine ) was great and amazing friendly. Really HK style compare to other Cafes.
Very good  place to get quick bites. And Very big portions!!
Excellent services, food is delicious, the crispy bun with pork is the one must eat, price is not expensive, super good deal, highly recommended
Be prepared to get way more than what you pay for because this place will provide you with exceptional service, quality and portion sizes!

One of the best HongKong style restaurants; Modern restaurant design, excellent food temperature and taste, free 2 hrs street parking right in front of the restaurant, and trendy cantopop music. Highly recommend its Milk Tea and Laksa soup base!
I ordered their pork chop bun. It comes with two porkchops and more fries than I could eat. Sugoi

My new fav HK breakfast place! They are so friendly and nice. They clean up the place really well in between customers too! Food came out in a good timely manner and they have great options on the menu too! The pricing isnt too bad either. Parking can be hard though but overall I thought it was worth it. Tasty and good portions!
Great portions of food. Everything was decent. Vegetarian options: Not suitable for vegetarians. No vegetarian menu. Food : 5/5 |

Very delightful lunch experience.  We order     (beat expectation)        (meet expectation)  pepper mushroom chicken combo with rice (beat expectation) . Remind me how hong kong style breakfast/lunch  is like. Service is fast and pleasant.  And they still keep 10% tip as their first tips option.   Very humble operation IMO. Will come back and highly recommended.

Used to he called Lim Kee when I was in high-school came back to find out their son took over the business. The son made great changes to the restaurant looks new and modern now. The food is STILL DELICIOUS. To my surprise the prices were great and lots of food. Quite nostalgic to come back here again
Lovely cozy joint for HK cafe-style comfort food staples. Generous portions for a great price. Friendly staff, clean sit down booths. Would recommend for a quick sit-down or no-fuss takeout!

Great neighborhood Hong Kong style cafe. My golden pork cutlet was super tasty especially with the curry sauce. My wifes vegetarian soup noodle was a bit bland though. Lots more choices on the menu at this new spot since we live nearby we will be trying many more of them. The owner is super nice and friendly.
strongly recommend! really comfortable restaurant, staffs are very friendly, service is great! strongly recommend milk tea and Lakas soup-based noodles! Food : 5/5

Holy cow. By far the cleanest cleanest sanitized hk style cafe I have ever been to.  Amazing. Very classic style food.  Tasty and exceptional value.  Highly recommend. I have never seen anyone wiping down the seats. Great service as well.  Highly recommend.

Run by a few young people. Good food and service. Like the way they have a waiting list board where you can put your name down.  And they actually call the names according to the list. The server asked me for opinions which is a very rare gesture in HK style cafe. Keep it up, guys.
Huge portions for cheap! Taiwanese nuggets were surfer flavourful and laksa was yummy
Good option to have a HK style food here.

First class customer service, definitely coming back for the breakfast and milk tea! You just have to experience this place. Not easy to describe over one comment and essentially closest place in Vancouver to get Hong Kong style cafe ambience

Pleasantly surprised by the good quality and taste of the food we ordered - Cream fillet pasta, Satay beef rice noodle and Takoyaki. A lot of HK style cafe in Vancouver / Richmond are usually mediocre but this place actually taste good. The staff there are friendly and often check on us.

Was my first time here, wasnt disappointed. The food was good, the service was excellent, you need to wait because there is usually a line for big groups but it was just a friend and me, so it was fast

Finally a legit HK style cafe around this neighbourhood. Nothing is more satisfying than a proper cup of HK style milk tea and this place delivers! I personally love the all-day breakfast selection. Lots to choose from the rice/spaghetti specials, food tastes great and the portions are generous. My go-to for lunch time.

Ive had their food for take out back in September. We tried going there once to dine in on Sunday without knowing closure on Sundays. Laksa and Porkchop on Rice were huge. My sister and I shared Laksa together and it was so filling we didnt eat Porkchop until the next day. L Food came out fresh and delicious. Iced Tea was also tasty. Porkchop came with plentiful of meat for take out. Laksa was pretty good. I had a great experience with Fat Boys Kitchen so this place is a must try.
Very nice authentic Hong Kong restaurant. The milk tea is great and the staff are very nice.
Foods are delicious and the staff is friendly !!
Beyond excellent services. Got to wait a bit , but it s all worth it for good food. Ordered the pork chop bun and satay noodles it was awesome ! Be back for sure !
pork
Good breakfast, friendly people
Friendly staff and great food. Portion sizes are great, especially the salt and pepper chicken rice. Always my go to for Hong Kong style food.
All the food Ive had at FBK has been fantastic. The laksa is spectacular and the sandwiches are amazing too.

Will definitely visit again. Food was awesome, servings were huge, and affordable. It also helped that their service was good. People who live in the Victoria Dr area are lucky to have this gem in their neighborhood...
Friendly service. Generous portions of very tasty food. I tried the Taiwanese chicken curry. Delicious. My bf tried the beef mushroom. Loved it
The honey tomato pork chop combo was a decent size and tasted great. Once I finished the pork chops there was still a lot of sauce so as I mixed it with my rice. Definitely going back.
Really tasty and affordable all day breakfast.
Surprisingly the dishes are high. Cannot finish and have to take out.
Food was delicious. Large portions. Small inside so be prepared to wait. Womans bathroom is tiny. Definitely recommend this place!
Great prices, good quality, tasty food, absolutely massive portions.  Highly recommend.  Im fortunate that it is a little out of the way for me to get to or I would be visiting too often
Best hk cafe in the city! Reasonable prices and very generous portions.
Super service and their menu combos are cheap and delicious! I had the Taiwanese chicken nuggets on rice and was very yummy :) I would recommend them for HK style/Taiwanese food
Super friendly service and love how they play the newest HK pop music on the TV. Solid HK style food.

Its a Hong Kong style restaurant with so many food choices. Clean environment, reasonable price, good food quality and tasty food. Hoping that the restaurant will open late in summer time like 8pm or so.
Went and tried their pepper chicken rice for take out. Very good flavors and taste. Excellent portions. Keep up the good work!
The pork bun was simple, absolutely delicious, and the fries were fantastic. The staff were very friendly.
Great atmosphere, service and the selections of delicious food will surely keep me coming back for more.
Prices are reasonable, foods are good quality and tasteful. Place and washroom are clean, owner and staff are very polite and courtesy.
Great food , good service
Great place to try HK food... amazing soups!
Cheap and good hk comfort food. Won t see prices like this anywhere else
tried the teriyaki chicken rice combo. Food was tasty. Good on quantity and polite guy at the restaurant. Recommend.
The food is really good. Excellent service. Worth to wait in line for.
Good food and excellent customer service for a Chinese restaurant!  Will definitely come back and refer friends!
Great food. Big portion. Will visit again.
w restaurant friend told me to come here I almost sued them because they were too good
Excellent beef steak with fries. More fries than you can imagine
Friendly service, clean and food yummy, I really like the bun. Crisper outside and soft inside.
